For a nanoparticle fixed size of Cu and Al2O3. It is remarked that Cu-MeOH nanoliquid is larger with heat transport when compared to Al2O3-MeOH nanofluid. Cu improves thermal conductivity by increasing fluid thermal conductance because it is a superior medium for heat transmission in a nanofluid than Al2O3. For those systems where heat transfer is most important, this behavior is recommended. The relative Nux\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
